   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Use this menu to set the cameras and the separation.<fig id="fig_o2b_bk3_fcc" class="- topic/fig ">
            <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                   placement="break"
                   align="center"
                   scale="50"
                   id="image_p2b_bk3_fcc"
                   class="- topic/image "/>
         </fig>
      </p>
      <section id="section_wyk_mrw_fcc" class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Camera Setup</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">For each camera (Main, Side, Side 2), set the gain. Adjust the gain percentages so that
            the camera images are not too dark and not too bright. (The brightness of the camera
            images can be adjusted.)<fig id="fig_wrj_ck3_fcc" class="- topic/fig ">
               <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                      placement="break"
                      align="center"
                      id="image_xrj_ck3_fcc"
                      class="- topic/image "/>
            </fig>
         </p>
      </section>
      <section id="section_l4r_4rw_fcc" class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Separation</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The ISWatch systems needs to separate camera images into bottle images.<ul id="ul_crh_td4_fcc" class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">By default, camera images are automatically separated into images of the bottle
                  (Automatic Separation activated).</li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">When halve bottle images are shown on the screen the automatic separation does
                  not work correctly, the separation should be done manually. </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Follow the steps described below. (See the image below.)<ol id="ol_l2t_5d4_fcc" class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">Deselect Automatic Separation.</li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">Press Show Graphs to get an intensity curves over one machine cycle.</li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">Set the Limit for each camera, the limit is shown in the graph with a red
                  line.</li>
            </ol>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">At the point where the intensity graph is higher than the red line (Limit value), the
            system will separate a bottle image.<note id="note_idf_xd4_fcc" class="- topic/note ">Do not set the limit too
               low, or too many bottles will be identified as stuck ware. Do not set the limit too
               high, or too many bottles will not be detected correctly. <fig id="fig_r33_lk3_fcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                         placement="break"
                         align="center"
                         scale="50"
                         id="image_s33_lk3_fcc"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </note>
         </p>
      </section>
